<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AP Clarifies Rabbi Story  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEWARK, N.J. (AP) -- In a July 14 story about abuse allegations
against Rabbi Baruch Lanner, The Associated Press gave an
incomplete account of the nature of the relationships he
acknowledged having had with some of his former female students.
</P>
<P>
   The story said he had acknowledged having ''physical
relationships'' with the women. It should have made clear that
Lanner said he had romantic, but not sexual relationships with the
women, and that the physical contact involved was limited to
hand-holding and putting arms around one another.
</P>
<P>
   Lanner said he violated Orthodox Jewish law by having these
relationships.
</P>
</TEXT>
