<HEADLINE> Teen charged with capital murder in shootings deaths  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) - One of two 18-year-olds charged with
robbing and shooting to death two teen-agers has been indicted on
first-degree murder charges, which carry a possible death penalty.
</P>
<P>
   Benjamin Switzer, 18, was indicted on capital charges Friday in
the slayings of William Barnwell, 18, and Eric Jenkins, 19. The
victims had been sitting atop a car sharing a pizza moments before
they were shot at close range near their homes on April 28.
</P>
<P>
   Switzer will be arraigned July 24 along with fellow suspect
Rommel Lewis, 18, who was charged with second-degree murder. They
were jailed without bail. Prosecutors must decide by Oct. 21
whether to seek the death penalty for Switzer.
</P>
<P>
   The victims were robbed of money and drugs but police said the
killings were not drug-related.
</P>
