<HEADLINE> Brooklyn restaurant worker fatally shot in robbery  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - A worker at a Brooklyn fast-food restaurant was
killed by a shotgun blast early Saturday during a botched robbery
attempt, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Mahbub Rahman, 27, of Brooklyn, was killed at about 1:30 a.m.
during the holdup inside Ala King Fried Chicken and Pizza on
Broadway in the Bushwick section, said police spokesman Alan
Krawitz.
</P>
<P>
   An unidentified bandit fired a shotgun at Rahman during the
robbery try, but the killer apparently fled without any cash,
Krawitz said. No arrests were made, and the investigation into the
homicide continued Saturday, he said.
</P>
