<HEADLINE> Richter Scale Wins DeFrancis Dash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAUREL, Md. (AP) -- Richter Scale broke the Laurel Park record
for six furlongs Saturday, winning the $300,000 Grade I DeFrancis
Dash in 1:07.95.
</P>
<P>
   Richter Scale, ridden by Richard Migliore, beat Just Call Me
Carl by 1&AMP;frac34; lengths. The 6-year-old horse paid $3.20 and $2.40 for
his first victory in a Grade I race.
</P>
<P>
   Dating to his win in the 1997 Derby Trial, Richter Scale is
8-for-8 when he has the lead after the first quarter in dirt races
at a mile or under.
</P>
<P>
   ''I had a lot of confidence in him. He's the best pure sprinter
I've ever been around in my life,'' Migliore said. ''I've never
been on a horse that does things quite so easy.''
</P>
<P>
   The $180,000 first-place prize put Richter Scale over the $1
million mark in earnings.
</P>
<P>
   Just Call Me Carl returned $3.20.
</P>
</TEXT>
