<DOCNO> APW20000715.0096 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-15 19:00 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Crew 2, Wizards 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Dante Washington and Jason Farrell scored
off corner kicks as the Columbus Crew beat the Kansas City Wizards
2-0 on Saturday in Major League Soccer.
</P>
<P>
   Washington scored his team-leading 14th goal in the 54th minute,
heading Robert Warzycha's pass to the right of goalkeeper Tony
Meola.
</P>
<P>
   In the 62nd minute, Warzycha sent a corner kick into the box and
Farrell, running toward the ball, headed it past Meola.
</P>
<P>
   The Wizards (11-4-5) managed just three shots on Columbus
goalkeeper Mark Dougherty. The Crew (9-10-4) had seven shots on
goal.
</P>
<P>
   Columbus has won four straight against Kansas City.
</P>
</TEXT>
