<HEADLINE> Milwaukee Brew Wins Ohio Derby  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NORTH RANDALL, Ohio (AP) -- Milwaukee Brew edged favorite Brave
Quest by a head Saturday in the $300,000 Grade II Ohio Derby for
3-year-olds at Thistledown.
</P>
<P>
   Milwaukee Brew, ridden by Michael McCarthy, ran 1 1-8 miles in
1:50.2, and paid $11.40, $5.20 and $3.60. Brave Quest returned $4
and $3.20, and Kiss a Native paid $4.60 to show.
</P>
<P>
   McCarthy, who won last year's Ohio Derby aboard Stellar Brush,
became the first jockey to win the race in consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
   Milwaukee Brew was bred in Kentucky by owner Frank Stronach, who
recently bought Thistledown. The win was worth $180,000 to increase
Milwaukee Brew's career earnings to $313,350.
</P>
</TEXT>
