<HEADLINE> Church Van Overturns, Kills Two  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONAHANS, Texas (AP) -- A church van returning from a missionary
trip to Mexico overturned Saturday in western Texas, killing two
passengers and injuring five others, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The passengers, all adults, were returning to Porterdale, Ga.,
when the van's driver lost control after his leg cramped, state
trooper Eric White said. The van rolled twice, ejecting several
passengers, he said.
</P>
<P>
   White identified the victims as Dillon Smith, 70, of Blakely,
Ga., and Matthew Philip Allen, 27, of Covington, Ga. Two others in
the van were hospitalized in serious condition Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   The wreck happened about 6 a.m. along Interstate 20 near
Monahans, about 200 miles east of El Paso. White said the Methodist
church members had been working in the Mexican state of Chihuahua.
</P>
