<HEADLINE> Hurricane Bertie Wins at Calder  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Hurricane Bertie beat Bourbon Belle 2&AMP;frac12; lengths
Saturday in the $400,000 Grade III Princess Rooney Handicap, the
highlight of a six-stakes program at Calder.
</P>
<P>
   Five of the stakes were at sprint distances, from two furlongs
to six furlongs, carrying total purses of $950,000.
</P>
<P>
   Jockey Pat Day won the $200,000 Azalea Breeders' Cup on Swept
Away and the $40,000 Burst of Colors, a distance race, on Grand
Veranda. Corey Nakatani won the $200,000 Carry Back on Caller One.
</P>
<P>
   Hurricane Bertie ran six furlongs in 1:11 and paid $8, $5.20 and
$2.60. Bourbon Belle paid $4.40 and $3, and Cassidy paid $2.60 to
show. Hurricane Bertie, the 5-year-old daughter of Storm Boot,
capped a huge day for her owners, Richard Bartram and Elaine Klein,
as well as for Day and trainer Bernie Flint.
</P>
<P>
   Thirty minutes earlier, the same combination triumphed by 3&AMP;frac12;
lengths in the Azalea, also a Grade III event. Swept Away took the
lead on the last turn and brushed off a challenge from Precious
Feather at the eighth pole. Watchfull was third in the six-furlong
race for 3-year-old fillies.
</P>
<P>
   Swept Away was timed in 1:11 2-5 and paid $4.60, $2.60 and
$2.40. Precious Feather returned $4.20 and $3, and Watchfull paid
$3.80 to show. Swept Away, the daughter of Mystery Storm, has won
five of eight and $286,480.
</P>
<P>
   The Carry Back Stakes was an even bigger rout as Caller One, the
odds-on choice, breezed home by five lengths over Fappie's
Notebook. Malagot came from last to finish third in a field of nine
3-year-olds. Caller One put away Gadir on the stretch turn and was
all by himself through the drive.
</P>
<P>
   Caller One ran the fastest six furlongs of the day, 1:10 1-5,
and paid $3.40, $2.80 and $2.40. Fappie's Notebook returned $3.60
and $3, and Malagot paid $6.20 to show. Caller One, by Phone Trick,
has won six of nine starts with earnings of $358,237.
</P>
<P>
   Long shot Miners Gamble won the $100,000 Calder Turf Sprint
Handicap, a five-furlong race on the turf course. Ridden by
Sebastian Madrid, Miners Gamble finished 1&AMP;frac12; lengths in front of
Wertz. The winner was timed in 56 2-5 and paid $24.40.
</P>
</TEXT>
