<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-15 21:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rockers 79, Fever 55  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEVELAND (AP) -- Merlakia Jones scored 13 points, as five
Cleveland players scored in double figures in the Rockers' 79-55
victory over the Indiana Fever on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Jones, set to play in her second straight WNBA All-Star Game on
Monday night in Phoenix, hit her first three shots to spark
Cleveland (12-8) to an early lead.
</P>
<P>
   The Rockers never trailed and led by as many as 30 points en
route to their fourth consecutive victory and fifth in six games.
Cleveland pulled within one-half game of first-place Orlando in the
Eastern Conference.
</P>
<P>
   The expansion Fever (5-15) had their first two-game winning
streak snapped. Danielle McCulley led Indiana with 17 points.
</P>
<P>
   Rushia Brown and rookie Ann Wauters each scored 11 points and
Mery Andrade and Vicki Hall added 10 apiece for Cleveland. Wauters,
the first overall pick in this year's draft, also had a game-high
eight rebounds and three blocked shots.
</P>
<P>
   The Fever entered the game leading the WNBA in 3-point shooting,
making 37 percent. However, Indiana shot just 3-for-12 from behind
the arc, and was 19-for-52 (36.5 percent) on field goals overall.
</P>
<P>
   Cleveland, which shot 56.9 percent (33-for-58) dominated every
aspect of the game in rolling to a 39-19 lead at halftime.
</P>
<P>
   Steals by Andrade and center Chasity Melvin led to easy layups
at the other end that helped Cleveland take a 22-7 lead.
</P>
<P>
   After Jurgita Streimikyte scored on a six-foot jumper for
Indiana to make it 22-9, neither team scored for the next 4:34.
</P>
<P>
   Cleveland, which had a 7-25 mark last season, improved to 8-2 at
home.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
