<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-15 21:54 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cubs 8, Twins 4  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Sammy Sosa tied Joe DiMaggio for 50th place
on the career home run list, hitting No. 361 as the Chicago Cubs
beat the Minnesota Twins 8-4 Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Sosa connected in the second inning against Joe Mays for his
25th home run of the season. He homered for the second straight
day, and has hit four in eight games.
</P>
<P>
   Sosa's presence boosted the crowd to 36,688, the Twins' largest
at home since opening day.
</P>
<P>
   Kevin Tapani (6-7) pitched eight innings. He gave up 12 hits,
but helped himself by striking out nine and walking none.
</P>
<P>
   The Cubs won two of three at the Metrodome after taking two of
three against the White Sox. The Cubs have won consecutive series
for the first time this season.
</P>
<P>
   Matt Lawton went 4-for-4 with a homer and three RBIs for
Minnesota, which lost for the ninth time in 11 games.
</P>
<P>
   Tapani, who was with Minnesota from 1989-95, made his third
career start against the Twins and first at the Metrodome since
1996, when he pitched for the White Sox.
</P>
<P>
   Tapani pitched at least six innings for the 17th time in 20
outings.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota took a 1-0 lead on Lawton's RBI single in the first
inning.
</P>
<P>
   Sosa led off the second with a 417-foot shot off Mays (4-11).
</P>
<P>
   Henry Rodriguez followed Sosa's homer with a triple that center
fielder Jacque Jones lost in the white Metrodome roof. Two outs
later, Willie Greene hit an RBI single to make it 2-1.
</P>
<P>
   Ricky Gutierrez, Mark Grace and Sosa hit consecutive one-out
singles to load the bases in the third inning. Rodriguez then hit a
check-swing double off first baseman Ron Coomer's glove to score
two runs.
</P>
<P>
   Coomer, who hit an RBI double in the sixth, left in the eighth
because of a strained left shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Grace hit an RBI double in the fourth inning to make it 5-1.
</P>
<P>
   Jones lost another fly ball in the sixth inning, resulting in
Greene's leadoff triple. Brant Brown followed with an RBI single
and Eric Young hit a run-scoring double to make it 7-1.
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Reed hit an RBI double in the seventh off Johan Santana to
make it 8-2.
</P>
<P>
   Lawton, who tied his career high with four hits, hit a two-run
homer off Tapani in the eighth to make it 8-4.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Sosa's next targets on the career home run list are Ralph
Kiner (369) and Gil Hodges (370). ... Tapani, who is 2-0 against
Minnesota, has now appeared in 92 games at the Metrodome. He is
46-30. ... Rodriguez is 7-for-14 in last four games, with two
homers and 10 RBIs. ... Twins manager Tom Kelly missed his third
straight game to be with his father in Fort Myers, Fla. Joe Kelly
is recovering from a heart bypass operation. ... Lawton, who has
had four hits in a game nine times, has played in every game this
season and started all but one.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
