<HEADLINE> Burn 3, Fusion 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Ariel Graziano scored twice in the
first half as the Dallas Burn beat Miami 3-0 on Saturday night for
their first road victory of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Dallas improved to 9-11-3 overall and 1-9-2 on the road. Miami
is 7-10-4.
</P>
<P>
   Graziano scored in the 24th and 44th minutes to increase his
season total to 13. Eric Dade also scored for Dallas.
</P>
<P>
   Burn goalkeeper Matt Jordan made two saves in recording his
third shutout of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Kyle Becerkman, the 18-year-old midfielder who signed with Miami
on June 27, made his MLS debut in the 69th minute.
</P>
</TEXT>
