<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-15 22:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Woman, 62, accomplice, 75, charged with bank hit  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   SYRACUSE, N.Y. (AP) - Police have charged two senior citizens
with robbing a downtown bank.
</P>
<P>
   Eloise Bowman, 62, and James Redfearn, 75, may be the oldest
suspects Syracuse police have ever charged with bank robbery, Sgt.
David Sackett said.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's not very likely you'd see somebody that old arrested in a
bank robbery, or a felony like that,'' Sackett said.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Bowman and Redfearn each face felony charges of
robbery and grand larceny.
</P>
<P>
   Police say Bowman robbed KeyBank on May 10, passing a note
demanding cash. Police at the time said they were unsure of the
thief's gender because the robber appeared to have a woman's face
but a man's hands.
</P>
<P>
   Police say Redfearn drove Bowman from the scene. They did not
disclose how much cash was stolen.
</P>
<P>
   Detectives are investigating whether the pair might be involved
in other city bank robberies, Sackett said.
</P>
</TEXT>
