<HEADLINE> Euchre Wins Bel Air Handicap  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif (AP) -- Euchre, an 11-1 longshot, pulled away
from 17-1 longshot Sultry Substiute and favorite River Keen to win
the $150,000 Bel Air Handicap at Hollywood Park on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Euchre, ridden by Alex Solis, led by a head at the top of the
stretch before pulling away, covering 1 1/16 miles in 1:41 3/5 and
paying $25.80, $11.60 and $4.40.
</P>
<P>
   The 4-year-old gelding's win spoiled River Keen's bid to become
the race's first winner in consecutive years. The $90,000 winner's
purse raised Euchre's career earnings to $280,045.
</P>
<P>
   Sultry Substitute, ridden by Garrett Gomez, paid $15.60 and
$5.20. River Keen, ridden by Victor Espinoza, paid $2.80 to show.
</P>
