<HEADLINE> Wild Sign Draft Pick Marian Gaborik  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) -- The Minnesota Wild signed first-round
draft pick Marian Gaborik to a three-year contract Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Gaborik, 18, who flew back to his native Slovakia on Friday,
received a faxed copy of the deal on Saturday morning, signed it
and returned it, agent Allan Walsh said.
</P>
<P>
   The Wild needed to sign Gaborik by midnight EDT Saturday to
avoid paying a $100,000 penalty because of an agreement between the
NHL and the International Ice Hockey Federation.
</P>
<P>
   If an NHL team signs a player under a European contract after
July 15, the NHL team must pay a fee to the European club that owns
the player's rights. In this case, it would have been Dukla Trencin
of Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
   ''He feels very happy to be part of the Wild organization and
feels that the Wild are very classy and have treated him like
family from the moment they drafted him,'' Walsh said.
</P>
<P>
   Gaborik was the third overall pick in last month's entry draft.
The left wing scored 37 goals in two seasons in the Slovakian
Senior League.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-1, 185-pound Gaborik will come to North America in
mid-August to train in Los Angeles for about 10 days before joining
the Wild's inaugural training camp, Walsh said.
</P>
<P>
   Also Saturday, the Wild signed left wing Maxim Sushinsky, the
team's fifth-round pick last month, to a multiyear contract.
</P>
<P>
   Sushinsky, 26, was the second-leading scorer in the Russian
Elite League last season. He had 19 goals and 24 assists for
Avangard Omsk.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
